text: Oleksandra Lohviniuk (born 8 September 2001) is a Ukrainian track cyclist. She won the bronze medal in the team sprint at the 2020 UEC European Track Championships. She competed at the 2021 UCI Track Cycling World Championships, in the women's team sprint event. == References == Category:2001 births Category:Ukrainian cyclists Category:Living people
